Good afternoon Gurpreet, as previously discussed, unfortunately our contracts do not cover shock absorbers, so we will not be able to assist with this portion of the claim. Additionally, I can see grease on the cv shaft that you sent me a picture of, indicating that the boot is punctured or torn. Unfortunately we do not cover cv shafts with torn or punctured boots. Fortunately, the replacement of the right front lower ball joint and left front wheel bearing is covered. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, our contracts allow for a maximum of $250 for wheel bearing parts. If you choose to proceed with the quoted wheel bearing, the customer will have to pay the difference.
